  "prompt": "Can I graduate college with 1.8 GPA?",
  "response": "Graduating college with a 1.8 GPA is highly unusual and typically not possible, as most institutions have minimum GPA requirements to graduate, usually around 2.0 on a 4.0 scale. Here\u2019s what you need to know:\n\n1. **Institutional Policies**: Most colleges and universities require a minimum cumulative GPA (often 2.0) to earn a degree. A 1.8 GPA usually falls below this threshold and would disqualify you from graduating.\n\n2. **Academic Probation**: If your GPA is below the required threshold, you may be placed on academic probation. During this time, you\u2019ll need to raise your GPA to meet the minimum standard, or you risk being dismissed from the institution.\n\n3. **Options to Improve GPA**:\n   - Retake failed or low-graded courses to replace the original grades (if your school allows grade replacement).\n   - Focus on improving performance in future courses.\n   - Seek academic advising or tutoring to address any challenges.\n\n4. **Alternative Pathways**:\n   - If raising your GPA isn\u2019t feasible, consider transferring to a different institution with less stringent GPA requirements.\n   - Explore vocational or certificate programs that may not require a degree.\n\n5. **Communicate with Advisors**: Speak with your academic advisor to understand your school\u2019s specific policies and explore possible options.\n\nUltimately, graduating with a 1.8 GPA is unlikely, but taking proactive steps to improve your academic performance or exploring alternative pathways can help you achieve your educational and career goals.",
